      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Expressing an Apology"
        },
        "text": "Learn common phrases to apologize. \"آسِف/آسِفَة\" (āsif/āsifah) is a basic way to say \"sorry\".",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أَنَا آسِفٌ جِدّاً لِلتَّأْخِير.",
            "english": "I am very sorry for the delay. (Male speaker)",
            "transliteration": "Anā āsifun jiddan lil-ta'khīr."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أَنَا آسِفَةٌ لِأَنِّي أَزْعَجْتُكَ.",
            "english": "I am sorry for bothering you. (Female speaker to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Anā āsifatun li'annī azʿajtuka."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "اعْتَذِرُ عَمَّا حَدَثَ.",
            "english": "I apologize for what happened.",
            "transliteration": "Iʿtadhiru ʿammā ḥadatha."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Accepting an Apology"
        },
        "text": "Respond to an apology with grace and understanding.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لَا مُشْكِلَةَ أَبَداً.",
            "english": "No problem at all.",
            "transliteration": "Lā mushkilata abadan."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "لَا دَاعِيَ لِلِاعْتِذارِ.",
            "english": "No need to apologize.",
            "transliteration": "Lā dāʿiya lil-iʿtidhār."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "قَدْ حَدَثَ وَانْتَهَى الْأَمْرُ.",
            "english": "It happened and it's over.",
            "transliteration": "Qad ḥadatha wa-intahá al-amr."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
